ce:section.ce:para:
The structure, morphology, and size distribution of the as-prepared CQDs and CQDs/β CD/NIPAM@AA-Gal nanogels were synthetically analyzed via the SEM technique (Fig. 3
                           ). The accomplished SEM analysis demonstrated that all of the synthesized CQDs have a smooth surface with a regular spherical morphology and an average diameter near 4.1 nm. After coating of the CQGs via the free radical polymerization process in nanogels form and also their functionalization with D-Gal, the spherical morphology was preserved but the mean diameter was increased to ranging between 300 nm and 320 nm. The observed increase in the size could be related to the formed polymeric network and also the introduced D-Gal molecules in the nanogels structure and is in accordance with the observed SEM images of the published literature [50,51]. For further investigation, the morphological details of the CQDs/β CD/NIPAM@AA-Gal nanogels were also analyzed by TEM (Fig. 4
                           a). It can be seen that the nanogels presented monodispersed state that is important for biomedical applications. These results certified the successful fabrication of the CQDs/β CD/NIPAM@AA-Gal nanogels and their suitability for biomedical applications.
